	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Randomizing NPC appearances</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=541492" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top">
		    <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    I noticed an interesting post on the developer forums today where a user made a relevant request to the dev team:<br>
<blockquote>
  mordea2 wrote:
        <p>A<b>ny chance for you guys to randomize the hair type/hair color/eye 
        color for both:<br>
        a) NPCs<br>
        b) people without Luclin or people who haven't yet chosen their styles?
        </b>
        </p>
        <p><b>I've read how you have matching faces depending on what face you 
        chose pre-new models which was a good idea, now applying it to the hair 
        would be a Good Thing. :-) </b> </p>
        <p><b>It looks a bit silly to have the entire city of Felwithe full of 
        identical red-headed ponytailed high elves. I guess it isn't really 
        noticeable for other races because a more "normal" color was chosen 
        (usually browns) but still.. not very realistic. </b> </p>
        <p><b>Anyway, it would be awesome if you randomized for NPCs and people w/o 
        Luclin, for diversity and realisticness all that keen stuff. :-) or at 
        the very least pick a neutral color. </b> </p>
        <p><b>Ok, I'll admit it, I'm partly biased because I am red-headed high elf 
        by choice (I'm a firey wizard with an attitude, you see, so it fit me 
        well), but it isn't so cool when everyone without Luclin (or more 
        generically everyone who hasn't chosen a new model face, not owning 
        Luclin or not) and ALL high elf NPCs show up exactly the same! </b> </p>
        <p>I don't really know about randomizing the look of folks that don't 
        have Shadows of Luclin. I don't know how that is being done. I'll have 
        to look into it. </p>
        <p>Unfortunately, right now all the old world NPCs do indeed have 
        default face and hair (if they have a new model – some are special 
        models that don't have new model equivalents and you still see the old 
        model –
        <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000431.html" target="_blank">
        you can read about that here</a>). </p>
        <p>We do plan to go back and assign new faces and hair to those NPCs. 
        But it's going to take some time, there are a lot of them to fiddle 
        with. Eventually we'll make it so that you are once again a rather 
        unique elf.
        <img src="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/smile.gif" width="15" height="15">
        </p>
